THE MAIN TWO STEPS OF ANY RECURSION CODE IS
1. THE BASE CASE
   this is the simplest possible version of the problem means that this is the condition you know which will be achieve in order to complete the solution and here you the answer already that what would the code return here.
   this part is to stop the recursive call and the it rollback
2. THE RECURSIVE STEP
   this is where the method call itself but with a smaller input and this call occurs again and again which must move closer to the base case with every call and eventually hit that base case condition.




THE CALL STACK
when you call a method in java, the computer puts it in a stack
PUSHING: each recursive call adds a new plate to the top.
WAITING: the bottom plates can not finish unitl the top plate is done.
POPPING: once the base case is hit, the plates are removed one by one, passing the result back down.




