TYPES OF RECURSION IN JAVA
1. DIRECT 
2. INDIRECT
3. TAIL (MOST OPTIMIZED)
4. HEAD
5. TREE

1. DIRECT RECURSION
a method call itself directly 

2. INDIRECT RECURSION
a method call another method which then call the first method back again
method a call method b and method b call method a

3. TAIL RECURSION
the recursive call is the last statement of the method
there is no pending work left after the call returns

4. HEAD RECURSION(NO-TAIL)
this is opposite 
the recursive call is not the last statement of the method
some task are performed after the call

5. TREE RECURSION
instead of calling itself once the method calls itself two or more times
creating branches effect
